last_episode_to_air.name: The Hong Kong Longs
last_episode_to_air.overview: Jake and the entire family head to Hong Kong for summer vacation, but must face off against the dreaded Dark Dragon when Grandpa is kidnapped.

name: American Dragon: Jake Long
overview: American Dragon is a coming of age comedy-action series about Jake Long, a 13-year-old Asian-American boy who strives to find balance in his life as a skateboard-grinding, New York 'tween while learning to master his mystical powers (in his secret identity) as the American Dragon, the protector and guardian of all magical creatures secretly living amidst the human world.

episodes.name: Old School Training
episodes.overview: Jake gets fed up when Grandpa puts him through a series of disgusting and seemingly pointless training exercises.

episodes.name: Dragon Breath
episodes.overview: When Jake comes down with a serious case of Dragon stank breath; Fu Dog must set him up on a date for the school dance.

episodes.name: The Talented Mr. Long
episodes.overview: Jake must compete in the school talent show with Fu Dog as his ventriloquist sidekick.

episodes.name: The Legend of the Dragon Tooth
episodes.overview: Dr. Diente, the Tooth Fairy's assistant gone bad, needs Haley's first baby tooth in order to activate his doomsday tooth monster. Jake must save his sister and the day.

episodes.name: Act 4, Scene 15
episodes.overview: Wanting to get some lip-on-lip action with the honey of his dreams, Jake butchers the role of Antony to play opposite Rose's Cleopatra in the school play.

episodes.name: Adventures in Trollsitting
episodes.overview: Jake must comedically hide a giant, hairy troll in his apartment for an entire day.

episodes.name: Fu Dog Takes a Walk
episodes.overview: Fu must tangle with an evil dogcatcher in order to make his way to a baseball game.

episodes.name: Professor Rotwood's Thesis
episodes.overview: Desperate to collect reward money to replace Trixie's mother's broken one-of-a-kind vase, Jake embarks on an attempt to provide Professor Rotwood with proof of the existence of dragons.

episodes.name: The Egg
episodes.overview: The Egg: When a rare Griffin egg is stolen, Jake must fight the Huntsclan to return it to its nest.

episodes.name: The Heist
episodes.overview: Jake, Grandpa, Trixie, Spud, and Fu Dog must comically stumble through an elaborate "Ocean's 11" style heist to retrieve a Leprechaun's stolen gold.

episodes.name: Dragon Summit
episodes.overview: Jake risks losing Grandpa as his dragon master and must face the most terrifying villain of all - a dragon gone bad.

episodes.name: Body Guard Duty
episodes.overview: When Jake is assigned as body guard  to the Oracle Twins, their incessant visions of the future drive him nuts -- until he realizes they can use their powers to make his life easier.

episodes.name: Shapeshifter
episodes.overview: When Jake gets shape-shifting powers for a dragon mission, he misuses them to get out of a parent-teacher conference and impress his peers.

episodes.name: The Ski Trip
episodes.overview: When Jake, Trixie, and Spud attend a school sponsored ski trip, Jake embarks on an investigation to find out the true identity of the Huntsgirl, while also trying to get some alone time with Rose.

episodes.name: The Long Weekend
episodes.overview: Jake must stop the legendary Jersey Devil from terrorizing the woodland village of earth sprites.

episodes.name: Eye of the Beholder
episodes.overview: Fu Dog is forced to go undercover as a contestant in the "Miss Magical World." beauty pageant.

episodes.name: Jake Takes the Cake
episodes.overview: A Gremlin on the loose at Mom's big catering gig threatens to disrupt the wedding of the century.

episodes.name: Hong Kong Nights
episodes.overview: Jake discovers that his ancient, out of touch Grandfather was once a swinging, stylin' Bruce Lee/Austin Powers-style mack daddy super-agent in 1960s Hong Kong. When Grandpa is captured by the Dark Dragon, Jake must face off against his arch foe to save him.

episodes.name: The Halloween Bash
episodes.overview: While Grandpa takes Haley trick or treating, Jake seizes the opportunity to throw the wildest Halloween party ever - mixing humans and magical creatures.

episodes.name: Fu and Tell
episodes.overview: Fu Dog must endure the extreme indignity of Haley's elementary school class "Show And Tell", while also confronting an old nemesis.

episodes.name: Flight of the Unicorn
episodes.overview: Jake, Trixie, and Spud must transport a wild mystical female unicorn from Coney Island to Central Park during holiday rush hour whilst escaping from the freakshow carnival folk.

episodes.name: Keeping Shop
episodes.overview: When Grandpa and Jake leave New York City, Trixie and Spud are forced to don a dragon costume and comically stumble their way through the American Dragon's duties.

episodes.name: Ring Around the Dragon
episodes.overview: Jake must rescue Hobie, an eight-year-old, 400-pound giant, from the evil clutches of King Hammer, owner of the K.E.W.L. (King Extreme Wrestling League).

episodes.name: The Hunted
episodes.overview: Jake is thrown together with a group of comically inept magical misfits when they are captured and chained together as the targets for the Huntsclan's annual hunting contest.

episodes.name: Bring It On
episodes.overview: When Jake faces a villain named Fury, who tries to find her sisters and rule the world once again, Trixie goes undercover as a cheerleader to get information from a tight-knit squad of cheerleaders who get possessed by Fury now and again.

episodes.name: Half Baked
episodes.overview: Jake decides to use a potion to locate Rose but when the contents end up in cupcakes baked for the school carnival, and everyone is turned into Krylock monsters, trouble ensues.

episodes.name: The Academy
episodes.overview: Jake and Spud stumble upon Rose while undercover at a secret Huntsclan Training School.

episodes.name: The Doppelganger Gang
episodes.overview: When Jake is overwhelmed by his hectic schedule, he begins using his dragon powers to create doppelganger copies of himself to help ease the load-with, but also creates his dark side who has plans of his own.

episodes.name: Something Fishy This Way Comes
episodes.overview: Jake's life is thrown into chaos when Grandpa starts dating his principal. Meanwhile, Jake learns a ferocious beast is preying on magical creatures.

episodes.name: Breakout
episodes.overview: Jake becomes obsessed with his appearance when he is hit by a vicious case of dragon acne. At the same time, he must work with Rose for the first time when she reveals the Huntsman's ultimate evil plan.

episodes.name: Family Business
episodes.overview: When Haley begins her dragon training, the sibling rivalry between Jake and Haley begins to erupt.

episodes.name: Hero of the Hourglass
episodes.overview: Jake time-travels back to the year 1986 to tell a teenage Dad the truth about magical creatures. But when Dad freaks and breaks up with Mom, it's up to Jake to get his parents back together.

episodes.name: Dreamscape
episodes.overview: Jake uses his ability to enter people's dreams to both comical and nightmarish results.

episodes.name: A Befuddled Mind
episodes.overview: Spud gets a perfect score on a government issued standardized exam at school and is recruited to a special top-secret school called "The Genius Institute". He soon discovers that there's more to the school than meets the eye.

episodes.name: Fool's Gold
episodes.overview: Jake gets sucked into the bling-bling lifestyle when he starts working for a semi-shady leprechaun clan.

episodes.name: Feeding Frenzy
episodes.overview: When the Longs attend a Florida family reunion, Jake must deal with his annoying cousin Greggy and an aquatic villain bent on flooding half the continent.

episodes.name: Haley Gone Wild
episodes.overview: Jake accidentally turns Haley on to the life of rebel wild child, with the help of a twisted magical children's show host who's much more sinister than he seems.

episodes.name: Supernatural Tuesday
episodes.overview: Jake's bid for student body president takes an unexpected turn when he uses a magical helmet to read the minds of his constituents.

episodes.name: The Rotwood Files
episodes.overview: Jake accidentally gets Rotwood fired, and ends up with a Principal who's even worse, meanwhile Spud tries to "woo" Stacey with onions.

episodes.name: Hairy Christmas
episodes.overview: Jake, feeling humiliated by his family's Christmas traditions, turns his back on them. But when he rescues a baby Sasquatch who was accidentally separated from his family, he learns the true meaning of Christmas.

episodes.name: Switcheroo
episodes.overview: An enchanted mirror switches the bodies of Jake and Haley for a day.

episodes.name: The Love Cruise
episodes.overview: When Cupid goes on vacation, he leaves his magical bow and love arrows in Grandpa's care. Jake can't resist borrowing Cupid's equipment and using it to play matchmaker on his school's "Love Cruise".

episodes.name: Year of the Jake
episodes.overview: While volunteering to mind Grandpa's shop on Chinese new year, Jake accidentally curses it with bad luck and must face the consequences.

episodes.name: Homecoming
episodes.overview: Jake tries to use his nomination as Homecoming Prince to win back Rose.

episodes.name: Young At Heart
episodes.overview: When Jake's youth is stolen by a magical creature, he makes the most of life as a 21-year-old... until he realizes that being a grown-up isn't all fun and games.

episodes.name: Siren Says
episodes.overview: Jake is "won" at a school bachelor auction by two girls-one pretty, one plain. He gravitates toward the pretty one, despite Trixie, Spud, Fu and Grandpa's fears that she is the siren bent on his destruction.

episodes.name: Shaggy Frog
episodes.overview: Spud is bitten by a magical frog, and begins to develop cool "froggy" powers. He enjoys all the perks of being part magical-that is, until #88 and #89 come 'a magical frog huntin'.

episodes.name: Nobody's Fu
episodes.overview: Jake's loyalty to Fu Dog comes into question when he's assigned a new animal guardian-a totally cool hip-hop helper monkey. But can Jake's perfect new pet ever take the place of Fu Dog?

episodes.name: Magic Enemy #1
episodes.overview: Jake's venting to an online journal unintentionally turns Rotwood into the magical world's public enemy #1.

episodes.name: A Ghost Story
episodes.overview: Jake, Spud, and Trixie become camp counselors. Jake must face his school nemesis Brad, as well as clan of ghosts, bent on revenge.

episodes.name: Bite Father, Bite Son
episodes.overview: Dad drags Jake to the office for Take Your Child to Work Day. Jake begins the day convinced that Dad's a wimp, but witnesses his father's inner (and outer) strength against a pack of marauding vampires.

episodes.name: Game On
episodes.overview: Frustrated by life's unexpected twists and turns, Jake uses a magical device which gives him the cheat codes to a perfect life. Of course, comical disastrous results ensue.

episodes.name: Furious Jealousy
episodes.overview: When Stacey and Nigel become an item, a jealous Spud decides to do anything to win her affection... including striking an unholy deal with Fury, the sinister gorgon.

episodes.name: Being Human
episodes.overview: With middle school graduation looming, a stressed Jake decides to give up his dragon powers and let Haley become the new American Dragon. But when an old foe returns, is Haley up to the task?

episodes.name: The Hong Kong Longs
episodes.overview: Jake and the entire family head to Hong Kong for summer vacation, but must face off against the dreaded Dark Dragon when Grandpa is kidnapped.
